duction of the »new world«. As such, the analysis of the use of »global« provides fascinating insights into an influential and politically loaded aspect of contemporary imaginations of the world.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2016: Frontlist Collection  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGlobalizationxPolitical aspects. 0aGlobalizationxSocial aspects. 4aCulture. 4aGlobalization. 4aInternational Relations. 4aPolitical Discourse. 4aPolitical Language. 4aPolitical Science. 4aPolitical Theory. 4aPolitics. 4aRhetorics. 4aThe New World. 4aUSA. 4aUncertainty. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Globalization.2bisacsh  aCulture.  aGlobalization.  aInternational Relations.  aPolitical Discourse.  aPolitical Language.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.  aRhetorics.  aThe New World.  aUSA.  aUncertainty.2 aKnowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2016: Frontlist Collectionefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066154540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839428962zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839428962zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839428962/original  a978-3-11-066154-5 transcript English Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-070100-5 DG Plus eBo